cs.SI, cs.DL, cs.SD, cs.IR, cs.SY 

The paper deals with the transformation of bibliographic networks based on temporal quantities, which is a topic related to social informatics (cs.SI) and digital libraries (cs.DL). The use of temporal properties of nodes, links, and their groups also suggests a connection to social dynamics (cs.SD) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the study of evolution in bibliographic networks can be seen as a problem in systems and control (cs.SY).
